<div id="review_3681056459" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3681056459" />
    <a title="PorshaJo" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5464046-porshajo"><img alt="PorshaJo" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1451425289p2/5464046.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3681056459?book_show_action=true">Dec 18, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="PorshaJo" class="user" itemprop="url" name="PorshaJo" href="/user/show/5464046-porshajo">PorshaJo</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5464046-porshajo?shelf=agatha-christie">agatha-christie</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5464046-porshajo?shelf=audio">audio</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5464046-porshajo?shelf=buddy-reads">buddy-reads</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5464046-porshajo?shelf=challengereads">challengereads</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5464046-porshajo?shelf=challengereads-2020">challengereads-2020</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3681056459" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15688726384652653270">Always great to revisit a known author, Agatha Christie, get in another Poirot mystery, and confirm to me that I can NEVER guess who the killer is. Ha! But it&apos;s always a great ride!<br/><br/>Simeon Lee is a wealthy, cranky, old man. It&apos;s a few days before Christmas and he has called all his remaining family members to his house for the holidays. One by one they assemble, most of which are not happy about this. He wants to toy with his family about inheriting his fortune. He spews nasty remarks constantly </span>
  <span id="freeText15688726384652653270" style="display:none">Always great to revisit a known author, Agatha Christie, get in another Poirot mystery, and confirm to me that I can NEVER guess who the killer is. Ha! But it's always a great ride!<br /><br />Simeon Lee is a wealthy, cranky, old man. It's a few days before Christmas and he has called all his remaining family members to his house for the holidays. One by one they assemble, most of which are not happy about this. He wants to toy with his family about inheriting his fortune. He spews nasty remarks constantly to each of them. But then things don't go as he planned when one of them whacks him. Just so much blood from this murder. But Poirot appears on scene and one by one he talks to each of the people that are in the house to ultimately find out what happens on this Christmas murder!<br /><br />What a joy this one was. It was a buddy read with Dana and we both really liked this one. We went with the audio and the narrator, Hugh Fraser, is wonderful. Not my first audio by this narrator nor my last. Obviously this wasn't the feel good Christmas book but one that we both enjoyed during the holidays! My only issue was too many people, many of which are not who they appear to be, and there is no way I could have ever figured this one out. But then again, I don't think I've ever guessed the murderer in any Christie book. But I can't wait to read the next one! <br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="15688726384652653270" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


