<div id="review_2629467714" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2629467714" />
    <a title="luce" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/9429655-luce"><img alt="luce" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1624808770p2/9429655.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2629467714?book_show_action=true">Dec 18, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="luce" class="user" itemprop="url" name="luce" href="/user/show/9429655-luce">luce</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Audiobook " href="/book/show/20409357-hercule-poirot-s-christmas">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/9429655-luce?shelf=owned-audiobooks">owned-audiobooks</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/9429655-luce?shelf=2020-reviews">2020-reviews</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/9429655-luce?shelf=re-reads">re-reads</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/9429655-luce?shelf=iii-favourites">iii-favourites</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/9429655-luce?shelf=2018-reviews">2018-reviews</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/9429655-luce?shelf=own">own</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2629467714" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8124423010856760795">I just love it when Poirot roasts the so-called genteel folk.<br/><br/><blockquote>“That was stupid; but you are, if you will pardon my saying so, rather a stupid man!”</blockquote> <br/> <br/><i>Hercule Poirot&apos;s Christmas</i> is the perfect holiday comfort read. It has many of Christie&apos;s classic trademarks: wealthy family, dispute amongst relatives, a will, despotic head of the family, sibling tiffs, red-herrings, some Shakespeare references, a creepy male relative eying up his young female relation (okay, maybe I could have done without this la</span>
  <span id="freeText8124423010856760795" style="display:none">I just love it when Poirot roasts the so-called genteel folk.<br /><br /><blockquote>“That was stupid; but you are, if you will pardon my saying so, rather a stupid man!”</blockquote> <br /> <br /><i>Hercule Poirot's Christmas</i> is the perfect holiday comfort read. It has many of Christie's classic trademarks: wealthy family, dispute amongst relatives, a will, despotic head of the family, sibling tiffs, red-herrings, some Shakespeare references, a creepy male relative eying up his young female relation (okay, maybe I could have done without this last one). The Christmas setting made this even more of an entertaining read. While they murder-mystery may not be the most complex one concocted by the queen of crime, I had a fun time seeing how things unfolded. And Christie simply excels when depicting family drama. I appreciated that the brothers in this novel pale in comparison to the various female characters (I mean, these boys ain't the sharpest tools in the shed). We also get the Mediterranean character who is just so exotic and sexy (warmer climate=hot blood=passionate=propensity to commit crimes of passion...yep, the logic holds up). Thankfully Christie also loves to poke fun at the inhabitants of Albion.<br />The dialogue is witty, the drama amusing, and Poirot himself is as delightful as ever.<br />I listened to the audiobook narrated by Hugh Fraser, and his voice perfectly rendered the tone and characters of the novel.</span>
  <a data-text-id="8124423010856760795" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


